metadata.description:
Decades in the Making on Manifold highlights the Eruption of Mauna Loa. The largest active Volcano on the planet. Shortly before Midnight on 11/27/2022 Lava Emerged filling the Caldera 13,000 ft a top Mauna Loa Summit. This event was the very first eruption in nearly 39 Years. Last eruption from Mauna Loa was in March of 1984. Mauna Loa cover half the Island and Elevation is 13,679ft.  
This Historic event only lasted days ending 12/13/2022
